name: Jordan Thompson
summary: Australian tennis player Jordan Thompson has made history at the 2024 US Open, stunning the seventh seed, Poland's Hubert Hurkacz, in the second round. This marks a significant achievement for the Aussies, as they had not advanced past the first round of the men's singles event in over two decades. Thompson's victory also means that for the first time since 1997, three Australian men have reached the third round of a Grand Slam tournament.

name: Novak Djokovic
summary: Novak Djokovic, ranked number one in the world, is aiming to secure a record-breaking 25th Grand Slam title at the 2024 US Open. Djokovic, who has already won 23 majors, has made a strong start to the tournament with a clinical first-round victory. He is scheduled to play in the night session on day one of the US Open, anchoring the evening program. Djokovic's withdrawal from the Miami Open has raised questions about his fitness, but he has since recovered and advanced to the third round with a retirement victory. The US Open is Djokovic's last chance to add to his Grand Slam tally in 2024, and he faces stiff competition from top players such as Carlos Alcaraz, Iga Swiatek, and Coco Gauff. Despite the challenges, Djokovic remains determined to make history and become the most successful male tennis player of all time.
